	(123,'Regent to fly Kolkata, Singapore ',NULL,'',NULL,'<p>Dhaka, 31 October 2013: After successful operations in Kuala Lumpur and Bangkok this year, Regent Airways is going to start its third and fourth International destinations - Kolkata and Singapore- respectively. The direct connectivity with Kolkata begins November 18 while Singapore will be connected on December 14.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dhaka-Kolkata daily flights will be started from November 18, 2013. The maiden flight of this route will depart from Dhaka at 08:45 am (local time) and will reach Kolkata at 09:00 am (local time). The return flight will depart Kolkata at 9:40 am (local time) and will reach Dhaka at 10:55 am (local time). Meanwhile, Regent Airways will launch Dhaka-Singapore flight on 14 December. It will operate 5 flights in a week (MON, TUE, THU, FRI &amp; SAT). The maiden flight will be departed from Dhaka at 12:20 PM (local time) and will reach Singapore at 18:35 pm (local time). The Return flight will start from Singapore at 19:25 pm (local time) and reach Dhaka at 21:40 pm (Local time).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The customers can purchase Kolkata economy class ticket starting from Tk 11,395 (round trip) and business class ticket at Tk 21,007 (round trip) and Singapore economy class ticket starting from Tk 35,938 (round trip) and business class ticket at Tk. 52,061 (round trip), inclusive of all govt. taxes. The tickets can be purchased through Regent&rsquo;s authorized travel agents, Regent Airways sales offices and Regent Airway&rsquo;s website www.flyregent.com.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The airline will operate flights with its&rsquo; newly acquired two Boeing 737-700 aircraft with 114 economy class and 12 business class seats. This will facilitate the passengers a comfortable feeling and enjoyable latest in-flight entertainments on board during the journey.</p>\r\n',NULL,'press','launches_dhaka_singapore_flights.jpg',NULL,'2016-02-02 04:19:23','2016-02-02 10:19:23',1,'','',2,NULL),
